measure.name: create_typical_building_from_model

measure.modeler_description: It is important that the template argument chosen for this measure is in line with the building types for the stub space types of the model passed in.

argument.name: hvac_delivery_type
argument.description: How the HVAC system delivers heating or cooling to the zone.

argument.name: htg_src
argument.description: The primary source of heating used by HVAC systems in the model.

argument.name: clg_src
argument.description: The primary source of cooling used by HVAC systems in the model.

argument.name: swh_src
argument.description: The primary source of heating used by SWH systems in the model.

argument.name: kitchen_makeup
argument.display_name: Kitchen Exhaust MakeUp Air Calculation Method
argument.description: Determine logic to identify dining or cafe zones to provide makeup air to kitchen exhaust.

argument.name: exterior_lighting_zone
argument.description: Identify the Exterior Lighting Zone for the Building Site.

argument.name: add_constructions
argument.description: Construction Set will be applied to entire building

argument.name: wall_construction_type
argument.description: Identify Exterior Wall Construction Type to be applied to entire building

argument.name: add_space_type_loads
argument.display_name: Add Space Type Loads to Model
argument.description: Populate existing space types in model with internal loads.

argument.name: add_elevators
argument.description: Elevators will be add directly to space in model vs. being applied to a space type.

argument.name: add_internal_mass
argument.description: Adds internal mass to each space.

argument.name: add_exterior_lights
argument.description: Multiple exterior lights objects will be added for different classes of lighting such as parking and facade.

argument.name: onsite_parking_fraction
argument.description: If set to 0 no exterior lighting for parking will be added

argument.name: add_exhaust
argument.description: Depending upon building type exhaust fans can be in kitchens, restrooms or other space types

argument.name: add_swh
argument.display_name: Add Service Water Heating to Model
argument.description: This will add both the supply and demand side of service water heating.

argument.name: add_thermostat
argument.description: Add Thermostat to model based on Space Type Standards information of spaces assigned to thermal zones.

argument.name: add_hvac
argument.description: Add HVAC System to the model

argument.name: add_refrigeration
argument.description: Add refrigeration cases and walkins model

argument.name: modify_wkdy_op_hrs
argument.description: Modify the weekday hours of operation in the model.

argument.name: wkdy_op_hrs_start_time
argument.description: Enter 24 hour values with fractional values converted to minutes. e.g. 17.25 = 5:15pm. Only used if Modify weekday hours of operation is true.

argument.name: wkdy_op_hrs_duration
argument.description: Length of weekday operating hours. Enter 24 hour values with fractional values converted to minutes. e.g. 17.25 = 5:15pm. Only used if Modify weekday hours of operation is true.

argument.name: modify_wknd_op_hrs
argument.description: Modify the weekend hours of operation in the model.

argument.name: wknd_op_hrs_start_time
argument.description: Enter 24 hour values with fractional values converted to minutes. e.g. 17.25 = 5:15pm. Only used if Modify weekend hours of operation is true.

argument.name: wknd_op_hrs_duration
argument.description: Length of weekend operating hours. Enter 24 hour values with fractional values converted to minutes. e.g. 17.25 = 5:15pm. Only used if Modify weekend hours of operation is true.

argument.name: unmet_hours_tolerance
argument.description: Set the thermostat setpoint tolerance for unmet hours in degrees Rankine

argument.name: remove_objects
argument.description: Only removes objects of type that are selected to be added.

argument.name: use_upstream_args
argument.description: When true this will look for arguments or registerValues in upstream measures that match arguments from this measure, and will use the value from the upstream measure in place of what is entered for this measure.
